        <head>
            <title>Three tourist places of kashmir</title>
        </head>
        <body>
            Kashmir is known for its beauty around the world, often called as paradise on earth.
            <p style="color: rgb(179, 83, 19);font-family: 'Franklin Gothic Medium', 'Arial Narrow', Arial, sans-serif;" >Kashmir is a beautiful 
            region known for its scenic landscapes, tranquil lakes, and lush valleys. Here are three important
            tourist places in Kashmir:</p>
            <p></p>
            <h2 style="color:darkmagenta">Srinagar:</h2>
            The summer capital of Jammu and Kashmir, Srinagar is famous for its picturesque Dal Lake, houseboats, Mughal Gardens, and vibrant
            markets.<p>The Shankaracharya Temple and Hazratbal Shrine are also notable landmarks. The houseboats on Dal Lake are a must-visit experience.</p>
            <h2 style="color:darkmagenta">Gulmarg:</h2>
            Known as the "Meadow of Flowers," Gulmarg is a popular hill station and ski resort in the winter. It offers breathtaking views of snow-covered <p>
            mountains and lush meadows, making it a favorite destination for adventure sports, especially skiing and snowboarding.</p>
            
            <h2 style="color:darkmagenta">Pahalgam:</h2>
            A serene town located along the Lidder River, Pahalgam is known for its natural beauty. Surrounded by pine forests and snow-capped mountains,
            <p> it serves as a base for pilgrims going to the Amarnath Cave and is also popular for trekking, fishing, and horse riding.</p>
            <p>
            These locations are just a glimpse of what Kashmir has to offer, with its majestic beauty and tranquil atmosphere.            
            </p>
        </body>
